  "title": "Senior FF&E Designer",
  "description": "<p>The Senior FF&amp;E Designer will be responsible for interior design and/or FF&amp;E space planning, architecture, articulating design intent through drawings, documents, sketches, and details development. The role involves bringing unique, immersive visual language to spaces through collaborative exploration and innovation.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Interior Design and FF&amp;E expertise.</li>\n  <li>Strong eye for detail and aesthetics.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in AutoCAD, Photoshop, SketchUp, MS Powerpoint, and related design software for design presentations and ID space planning.</li>\n  <li>Effective communication and presentation skills.</li>\n  <li>Tertiary education in Interior Design or related field.</li>\n  <li>Having an astute eye for material finishes, furnishings, colour stories, etc.</li>\n  <li><strong>Candidate must have </strong><u><strong>minimum 7 years of FF&amp;E experience, specifically in luxury hospitality ID projects</strong></u><strong>.</strong></li>\n</ul>",
